				\begin{document}$$proportionalrise={\rm{C}}7-{\rm{C}}0/{\rm{C}}11-{\rm{C}}0$$\end{document}proportionalrise=C7−C0/C11−C0 where C0, C7 and C11 represent concentrations on day 0, 7 and 11 respectively. For the Prior IPD group, we did not evaluate the responses of children to the (homologous) serotype that had caused their episode of disease, since this would represent an anamnestic response or demonstrate hyposresponsiveness hence confounding the results.
